news.title: Ramco Cements' net profit down 36.4% at Rs 109.23 crore in Q1 FY23
news.para: Its total income rose 44 per cent to 1,785.64 crore during the quarter under review against Rs 1,240 crore in the corresponding period of the previous fiscal.

news.title: Environmentalists say Rs 433 crore fine on illegal brick kiln units in Thadagam too little
news.para: The report, submitted on July 20, said that 1.1 crore cubic metres of brick earth was illegally mined and transported from 565 fields in Thadagam.

news.title: Corporation plans to cancel detailed town planning schemes in Thiruvananthapuram
news.para: ​The matter was included in the agenda of the council meeting held on July 14, which apparently was declared as passed amid the din. No discussion was held on the cancellation of DTP schemes in the city during the council meeting.

news.title: Mumbai: Nodal officers to ensure housing societies learn fire safety drill
news.para: The officer will also have to ensure that societies in coordination with designated associations and fire brigades hold training for their members in handling contingency situations, including how to douse a fire and evacuate residents.

news.title: Indore: Survey identifies 80,000 property tax irregularities
news.para: Owners of these propers declared less than the actual planning area of their respective properties in the self-declaration while obtaining building permission, said officials.

news.title: Gandhinagar development body to auction three plots in Kudasan, Sargasan, Vavol
news.para: The plots are in town planning schemes 6, 7 and 13. In the case of the plot in Kudasan, GUDA has fixed a base price of Rs 73,000 per sq m and is expected to yield Rs 40.43 crore.

news.title: DLF cuts net debt by 16% quarter-on-quarter to Rs 2,259 crore in Q1 FY23
news.para: On the operational front, DLF's sales bookings doubled to Rs 2,040 crore during the first quarter of this fiscal from Rs 1,014 crore in the year-ago period.

news.title: NOC for registrations: Delhi builders plan to approach housing ministry for relief
news.para: The order, issued in early July, has put on hold registration of high-value property transactions in Lutyens' Delhi, south Delhi and west Delhi. Many say the order is flawed.

news.title: Supertech twin towers to be 'charged' from tomorrow, site to turn into fortress
news.para: A high-level meeting of senior police officers, officials of Edifice Engineering and representatives of other stakeholders will take place on Monday to discuss the deployment of cops and other security arrangements at the site.

news.title: Mumbai property registration record streak continues, sees best July ever with 11,340 deals
news.para: The country’s commercial capital has recorded strong real estate sales momentum with over 11,340 registrations, brushing aside the concerns of rising interest rates and housing prices putting a dent in the pace of growth.

news.title: Haryana finalises draft for regularisation of 845 of 1,499 unauthorised colonies
news.para: According to information all the 845 colonies which will be deemed to be regularized for civic facilities exist within the jurisdiction of civic bodies.

news.title: Pune: Properties with solar water heating systems double in five years
news.para: While the number of properties with solar water heating systems stood at 29,000 in the year 2017-18, it surged to 58,000 in 2021-22, the report stated.

news.title: Hubballi-Dharwad civic body ranks second in digitisation of property records in Karnataka
news.para: The HDMC, which regulates the infrastructural assets and civic facilities in the twin cities of Hubballi and Dharwad including properties, transactions and their administration, had launched an online management system that keeps a record of property ownership, transactions and status.

news.title: DTP demolishes encroachments, illegal colony in Panchkula
news.para: District planning officer (DTP) Gunjan Verma said that the drive was conducted under the Controlled Urban Area Act and Urban Area Act of the Town and Country Planning department.

news.title: Municipal chiefs, additional DCs can now issue CLUs, approve layouts in Punjab
news.para: Building plans would be cleared by municipal commissioners in case of municipal corporations and EOs in case of municipal councils, nagar panchayats and improvement trusts.
